\[\frac{BD}{CD} = \frac{AB}{AC} = \frac{7}{5},\]so $\mathbf{d} = \frac{5}{12} \mathbf{b} + \frac{7}{12} \mathbf{c}.$

Similarly,
\[\frac{AE}{CE} = \frac{AB}{BC} = \frac{7}{3},\]so $\mathbf{e} = \frac{3}{10} \mathbf{a} + \frac{7}{10} \mathbf{c}.$

